name: Verify Document Name field is a free type text box and all characters and numbers can be entered
justification: Tests basic input functionality and data manipulation but does not cover critical process, security aspects, or multiple components.

name: Verify if Document Name field auto completes if there is a similar or same name used before
justification: Covers core functionality (document name auto-completion) and involves data manipulation. It's prone to errors, making it a candidate for regression.

name: Verify if user adds same or similar document name pop-up appears to alert the user about saving duplicate document name
justification: Verifies a critical process (preventing duplicate entries), has security implications, and involves user interaction with alerts. Prone to errors.

name: Verify the wording in the pop-up is user friendly
justification: Tests user interface language which impacts user experience but not core functionality or business-critical processes.

name: Verify the default tick box exists on the page and is usable
justification: Ensures basic UI functionality, doesn't involve critical processes or data manipulation, but ensures the correctness of UI components which is fundamental.

name: Verify when default is ticked, document appears in default document dropdown on maintenance page
justification: Tests a specific functionality that impacts the user experience and involves data manipulation with drop down menus.

name: Verify when default is not ticked, document appears in the client-specific document dropdown on the maintenance page
justification: Validates important dropdown functionality related to document management and client-specific data handling.

name: Verify the add functionality
justification: Covers the critical process of adding new documents, involves data manipulation, and ensures user input functionality works as expected.

name: Verify when document name is added, it shows on the table below
justification: Ensures that added data is correctly displayed, which is a fundamental functionality. Involves data manipulation and visual verification.

name: Verify the name of the columns in the document names table
justification: Tests basic UI consistency but does not cover critical or complex functionality.

name: Verify when document added, correct information is displayed on the table
justification: Validates that data integrity is maintained when displayed, a core aspect of data handling and management.

name: Verify the edit functionality on the document name table
justification: Ensures core CRUD functionality for documents, involves data manipulation, and has high business impact.

name: Verify the delete functionality on the document name table
justification: Critical for data management, involves data deletion which can affect system functionality. Ensures that delete operations work correctly.

name: Verify the delete functionality on the document name table when document name is used elsewhere in the system
justification: Ensures referential integrity and system stability when deleting documents used in other parts of the system. High priority and business impact.

name: Verify the search box above the document name table
justification: Tests a basic search functionality. Important for user experience, but not critical to core business processes.

name: Verify the page size dropdown above the document name table
justification: Tests basic pagination functionality, which is non-critical.

name: Verify the pagination below the document name table
justification: Similar to above, pagination is important but not critical for regression.

name: Verify all the spellings and alignment on the Document name maintenance page
justification: UI consistency check. Important for user experience but not critical for functionality.

name: Verify the user friendliness of the document name maintenance page
justification: Tests user interface and experience which is important but not a core functionality.

name: Verify responsiveness of the page when there is a large amount of data on the page
justification: Tests performance under load, which is important to ensure the system can handle large data.

name: Verify there is an expiry date applicable tick box on the default tab of the Worker document maintenance page
justification: Ensures the presence of a specific UI component. Important but not critical.

name: Verify expiry date applicable column is added to the table on the default tab worker document maintenance page
justification: Tests for UI consistency and data handling for expiry dates. Important for data integrity.

name: Verify document name is a drop-down on the Default tab and is feeding correctly from the document name maintenance page
justification: Validates core functionality of dropdown data integrity and linkage between different parts of the system.

name: Verify Documents can be added to the default document table
justification: Ensures critical data addition functionality works correctly which is essential for business processes.

name: Verify 'Click on more than one client to select multiple clients' message is displayed above the Select client dropdown
justification: Ensures the correctness of instructional messages. Important for usability but not critical for core functionality.
